00:34:27.106 --> 00:34:29.609
Nothing. just having
a personal conversation over here.

715
00:34:29.692 --> 00:34:32.487
Oh. well. don't mind me.
I'm just working over here.

716
00:34:32.570 --> 00:34:34.280
Would you care to join me?

717
00:34:34.363 --> 00:34:35.823
-Yeah. just...
-Thanks.

718
00:34:35.907 --> 00:34:37.533
Give me one second. Hmm.

719
00:34:38.284 --> 00:34:40.328
So he's a little protective of me.

720
00:34:40.411 --> 00:34:41.871
Is that what you call that?

721
00:34:41.954 --> 00:34:43.706
Just be nice.

722
00:34:43.790 --> 00:34:45.917
-He big man.
-Hey. hey. B. it's okay.

723
00:34:46.000 --> 00:34:47.919
[laughs] Let me give you my number.

724
00:34:48.002 --> 00:34:49.712
You had to let him smell you or something.

725
00:34:49.796 --> 00:34:52.048
Hey. Sonny. stop it.

726
00:34:52.131 --> 00:34:54.842
[Sonny] That is an incredible level to me.

727
00:34:55.551 --> 00:34:57.970
-Here. Call me. okay?
-Okay.

728
00:34:58.054 --> 00:34:59.931
-I'm damn sure gonna call you.
-Mmm-hmm.

729
00:35:00.014 --> 00:35:03.434
-Yeah. ha!
-[laughing] Shut up. you're so bad.

730
00:35:03.518 --> 00:35:05.269
Hey. I shouldn't show it to him. should I?

731
00:35:05.353 --> 00:35:06.646
No. Sonny...

732
00:35:07.396 --> 00:35:09.023
[Powers] We got eyes on you. Sonny.

733
00:35:09.649 --> 00:35:12.276
See you soon. Okay. go. go.

734
00:35:14.946 --> 00:35:17.406
What is y'all doing? We still open.

735
00:35:17.490 --> 00:35:19.700
This ain't no time
to congregate and socialize.

736
00:35:19.784 --> 00:35:21.661
Y'all get to cleaning this shit up.

737
00:35:22.245 --> 00:35:24.330
Everybody. Hey. man.
you just standing over there.

738
00:35:24.413 --> 00:35:26.207
Your hair looking wise.
you're not a wise man.

739
00:35:26.290 --> 00:35:27.959
Get... Get to picking something up.

740
00:35:29.293 --> 00:35:30.378
This is a business.

741
00:35:31.087 --> 00:35:33.714
Come on. man. we got to get
this stuff together. We still open...

742
00:35:33.798 --> 00:35:35.675
Hey. drop some more chicken.

743
00:35:35.758 --> 00:35:37.760
Get everything together.

744
00:35:37.844 --> 00:35:40.388
Sheesh! I'm telling you.

745
00:35:41.848 --> 00:35:43.307
Look. man.

746
00:35:43.391 --> 00:35:45.059
I know you ain't caught
yourself no attitude

747
00:35:45.143 --> 00:35:48.020
about this pterodactyl pit bull.
puppy-faced girl over here. man.

748
00:35:48.104 --> 00:35:49.730
She was a bad apple. She had to go.

749
00:35:49.814 --> 00:35:51.607
I just don't wanna talk about it
right now. okay?

750
00:35:51.691 --> 00:35:52.817
I can't do shit.

751
00:35:52.900 --> 00:35:54.902
It's some bullshit right here.
I just can't. man.

752
00:35:54.986 --> 00:35:56.654
We're in it bad because.
at the end of the day.

753
00:35:56.737 --> 00:35:58.447
I'm in here doing all the work I can. man.

754
00:35:58.531 --> 00:36:00.074
trying to get this restaurant
back together.

755
00:36:00.158 --> 00:36:01.951
-Mmm-hmm.
-[Sonny] Supposed to be all the glory.

756
00:36:02.034 --> 00:36:04.203
-And. I mean. every day...
-Hmm.

757
00:36:04.287 --> 00:36:06.330
Just follow my lead. man.
Stay outta my way.

758
00:36:06.414 --> 00:36:10.459
Just try not to be stumped
all the time. man.

759
00:36:10.543 --> 00:36:13.421
Man. you do stuff right the first time.
you won't have to do it...

760
00:36:13.504 --> 00:36:15.381
-Mmm.
-Over and over and over again.

761
00:36:15.464 --> 00:36:19.218
Don't you remember? They tell you that
when you was a little boy.

762
00:36:19.302 --> 00:36:21.429
Didn't nobody told you that
when you was a little boy. man?

763
00:36:21.512 --> 00:36:23.222
Listen. man. See. that's your problem...

764
00:36:23.306 --> 00:36:26.225
I get all this shit. man.
It's good. you know.

765
00:36:26.684 --> 00:36:28.227
You're damn. right. you know?

766
00:36:28.311 --> 00:36:29.604
Hallelujah!

767
00:36:29.687 --> 00:36:31.022
[laughing] Yeah!
Damn. we got this.

768
00:36:34.400 --> 00:36:36.235
You liking that new recipe. huh?

769
00:36:38.237 --> 00:36:40.948
Ooh. Boy. put that leg down.

770
00:36:41.032 --> 00:36:43.117
You thought you was gonna be back here
eating chicken all day?

771
00:36:43.201 --> 00:36:44.577
Don't be looking at me like that.

772
00:36:44.660 --> 00:36:46.954
-Why am I up here for?
-What do you mean?

773
00:36:47.038 --> 00:36:49.248
You could have gotten one of these cooks
to fix this shit.

774
00:36:49.332 --> 00:36:51.709
Do they own the establishment sign?

775
00:36:52.960 --> 00:36:54.587
No. put it over...

776
00:36:54.670 --> 00:36:57.256
No. tighten it up. See? Look at that.

777
00:36:57.340 --> 00:36:58.925
-[laughing]
-See? Look at it.

778
00:36:59.008 --> 00:37:02.178
My nigga. I knew you could do it. Ooh.

779
00:37:03.846 --> 00:37:05.723
Okay. I want everybody.
focus that attention.

780
00:37:05.806 --> 00:37:08.267
I need perfection and professionalism
on this floor.

781
00:37:08.351 --> 00:37:10.728
Now. these people come here
for one thing and one thing only.

782
00:37:10.811 --> 00:37:12.313
And it is not your pretty smile.

783
00:37:12.396 --> 00:37:14.398
It is Blazin' Jay's Fried Chicken.

784
00:37:14.482 --> 00:37:17.193
So I want these orders
turned around expeditiously.

785
00:37:17.276 --> 00:37:19.612
-[all] Yes. Chef!
-I need fresh chicken.

786
00:37:19.695 --> 00:37:23.491
fries and sides.
all in constant rotation.

787
00:37:25.618 --> 00:37:27.620
[Sonny] <i>Things were really</i>
<i>starting to look up.</i>

788
00:37:27.703 --> 00:37:29.455
<i>Blazin' Jay's was on fire.</i>

789
00:37:29.538 --> 00:37:31.582
<i>We could hardly keep up with the orders.</i>

790
00:37:35.336 --> 00:37:38.547
<i>Mama was still in the hospital.</i>
<i>The doctor say she getting better.</i>

791
00:37:38.631 --> 00:37:40.383
<i>And. with the restaurant doing so good.</i>

792
00:37:40.466 --> 00:37:42.635
<i>it seemed like she back</i>
<i>to her feisty self again.</i>

793
00:37:46.764 --> 00:37:49.058
<i>Even Sasha was taking notice.</i>

794
00:37:49.141 --> 00:37:50.434
[softly] Wow.

795
00:37:53.271 --> 00:37:56.315
I need all that chicken. I need that...
I need some more chicken fried.

796
00:37:56.399 --> 00:37:58.276
We done fell off back here. man.

797
00:37:59.110 --> 00:38:01.904
Stop bullshitting back there. man.
Get that chicken popping around here.

798
00:38:01.988 --> 00:38:04.991
I can't believe it took all this time
for me to get back here to you.

799
00:38:06.075 --> 00:38:08.077
I've missed you.

800
00:38:08.160 --> 00:38:09.620
-[chuckles]
-Not anymore.

801
00:38:10.538 --> 00:38:12.164
-Yeah. [laughs]
-Nom. nom. nom.

802
00:38:12.957 --> 00:38:14.250
Don't eat me!

803
00:38:25.928 --> 00:38:27.596
[Dutch] Oh. fuck!

804
00:38:30.766 --> 00:38:33.436
God damn it! Shit!

805
00:38:35.479 --> 00:38:36.856
[exhales]

806
00:38:44.655 --> 00:38:47.241
[Sonny] <i>I'm thinking business is booming</i>
<i>because of my changes.</i>

807
00:38:47.325 --> 00:38:51.329
<i>Meanwhile. Dutch taking our profits</i>
<i>to re-up on his little secret ingredient.</i>

808
00:38:51.412 --> 00:38:53.372
<i>I don't know how I didn't see it.</i>

809
00:38:57.960 --> 00:38:59.754
-[Sonny] Hey. hey. Dutch.
-What?

810
00:38:59.837 --> 00:39:02.006
Hey. you gonna need some more potatoes
over here.

811
00:39:02.089 --> 00:39:03.549
Oh. let's get them some potatoes.

812
00:39:08.179 --> 00:39:09.889
Pull up forward. pull up forward.

813
00:39:15.728 --> 00:39:18.022
Get the cars rolling. man.
Let's keep them cars rolling!

814
00:39:18.105 --> 00:39:19.440
Are you sending the ones
to the drive-thru?

815
00:39:19.523 --> 00:39:22.318
Yeah. go through the drive-thru.
We got the wings over there!

816
00:39:22.401 --> 00:39:23.944
-Okay.
-Hey. uh. what you trying to get?

817
00:39:24.028 --> 00:39:25.196
We got free drinks.

818
00:39:36.082 --> 00:39:38.584
-[police radio chatter]
-Hey. man. goodnight.

819
00:39:38.667 --> 00:39:39.960
Bye.

820
00:39:40.044 --> 00:39:41.420
[hip-hop music playing]

821
00:39:41.504 --> 00:39:43.589
Music. rims. gold teeth.

822
00:39:43.672 --> 00:39:46.675
Okay. that does not mean
they're drug dealers.

823
00:39:46.759 --> 00:39:48.219
I had a grill in high-school.

824
00:39:48.302 --> 00:39:50.513
-[chuckles] Don't remind me.
-[scoffs]

825
00:39:50.596 --> 00:39:53.057
You were always so square. man.

826
00:39:53.140 --> 00:39:56.894
I'm just saying. why waste your money
on flashy cars and jewelry?

827
00:39:56.977 --> 00:39:59.188
Oh. so if it was Queen Elizabeth

828
00:39:59.271 --> 00:40:02.149
driving by in her Rolls-Royce
and just dripping in rubies.

829
00:40:02.233 --> 00:40:04.819
-you'd be saying the same thing?
-That's different.

830
00:40:04.902 --> 00:40:08.239
-[scoffs]
-My point is. when I make some money.

831
00:40:08.322 --> 00:40:11.283
I'm gonna open a nice.
respectable business.

832
00:40:11.867 --> 00:40:13.786
Oh. like Blazin' Jay's.

833
00:40:13.869 --> 00:40:15.621
[scoffs] Yeah.

834
00:40:15.704 --> 00:40:17.957
-Like your boys at Blazin' Jay's.
-Mmm.

835
00:40:18.040 --> 00:40:19.750
The hate is strong with you. my friend.

836
00:40:21.210 --> 00:40:22.253
Sasha...

837
00:40:24.880 --> 00:40:27.174
I have some errands I have to run. but...

838
00:40:27.258 --> 00:40:29.218
I was hoping. maybe later.
you and I could grab a drink.

839
00:40:30.302 --> 00:40:32.763
Thanks for the invite
but I've got plans.

840
00:40:33.889 --> 00:40:35.224
Laundry night again?

841
00:40:35.307 --> 00:40:38.727
No. I've got a date.
thank you very much.

842
00:40:38.811 --> 00:40:41.105
-So a date. huh?
-Mmm-hmm.

843
00:40:41.188 --> 00:40:42.314
Night. partner.

844
00:40:45.067 --> 00:40:46.402
[sighs]

845
00:40:50.281 --> 00:40:52.533
-[Sasha giggles]
-[Sonny] Okay. so you know

846
00:40:52.616 --> 00:40:54.618
it's called paint and sip. right?

847
00:40:54.702 --> 00:40:58.372
[Sasha] Yes. but you're trying
to get me drunk over here. so...

848
00:40:58.456 --> 00:41:00.082
[Sonny] Like you could use
a little help over here.

849
00:41:00.166 --> 00:41:02.126
-Shut up. this looks good.
-[laughs]

850
00:41:02.209 --> 00:41:04.336
[chuckles] There's something to it.

851
00:41:04.420 --> 00:41:07.423
-Mmm.
-See? She likes it.

852
00:41:07.506 --> 00:41:10.050
-I bet she do like it.
-[laughs] You're so bad.

853
00:41:10.134 --> 00:41:12.011
Be the brush.

854
00:41:12.094 --> 00:41:13.721
-Feel the stroke.
-Shh!

855
00:41:13.804 --> 00:41:16.348
-What?
-[whispers] She's gonna hear you.

856
00:41:16.432 --> 00:41:18.726
She need to feel the stroke.

857
00:41:18.809 --> 00:41:21.395
[stammers] We gonna feel the stroke. shh.

858
00:41:21.479 --> 00:41:24.899
It doesn't seem like she felt a stroke
in quite some time.

859
00:41:26.025 --> 00:41:28.944
Mmm. well. I feel her pain.

860
00:41:29.862 --> 00:41:30.863
No.

861
00:41:31.697 --> 00:41:34.408
-You serious?
-Yes.

862
00:41:34.492 --> 00:41:37.119
-What?
-Being a cop doesn't really allow

863
00:41:37.203 --> 00:41:40.164
-much of a love life. so...
-Why not?

864
00:41:41.290 --> 00:41:44.126
I don't know. Partially. the hours.

865
00:41:44.210 --> 00:41:48.297
And I think it's because men
are intimidated by my job.

866
00:41:48.380 --> 00:41:50.466
-Well. boys. maybe.
-[Sasha chuckles]

867
00:41:51.258 --> 00:41:54.637
Plus. dating cops hasn't really
worked out too much for me either.

868
00:41:54.720 --> 00:41:57.348
[chuckles] Must suck for your boy. Powers.

869
00:41:58.140 --> 00:42:00.226
-Be nice.
-Why should I?

870
00:42:00.309 --> 00:42:02.394
-[laughs]
-He's nice.

871
00:42:02.478 --> 00:42:05.147
-To who?
-[laughing]

872
00:42:06.273 --> 00:42:09.360
-Mmm.
-You know. I always wanted to know.

873
00:42:09.443 --> 00:42:11.695
have you ever thought
about being anything else?

874
00:42:11.779 --> 00:42:13.489
Mmm-mmm. no.

875
00:42:13.572 --> 00:42:16.617
I love my job. Plus. you know my family.

876
00:42:16.700 --> 00:42:19.328
We're all cops.
It's just... It's just what we do.

877
00:42:20.037 --> 00:42:21.163
Yeah.

878
00:42:21.830 --> 00:42:26.085
I understand what you're saying.
and. while my work doesn't seem

879
00:42:26.168 --> 00:42:30.172
nearly as important as yours.
I do understand the pressures

880
00:42:30.256 --> 00:42:32.675
-of following in your family's footsteps.
-Mmm-hmm.

881
00:42:33.717 --> 00:42:36.011
You know. my grandpa. Johnny.

882
00:42:36.095 --> 00:42:38.764
he was a traveling blues musician.

883
00:42:38.847 --> 00:42:41.976
And legend has it
that he played the guitar

884
00:42:42.059 --> 00:42:47.064
so good and so fast.
that they started calling him Blazin' Jay.

885
00:42:47.147 --> 00:42:49.108
-Wow.
-[chuckles]

886
00:42:49.191 --> 00:42:51.068
Yeah. and...

887
00:42:51.151 --> 00:42:53.696
And when he got tired of the road.
he settled here.

888
00:42:53.779 --> 00:42:56.615
and that's how we ended up
with the Chicken Shack.

889
00:42:56.699 --> 00:43:00.035
[laughs] Wow. how come
you never told me this before?

890
00:43:00.119 --> 00:43:02.788
Well. maybe because I was too busy
sneaking in and out of your house.

891
00:43:02.871 --> 00:43:06.292
-trying to avoid your father.
-[laughing]

892
00:43:06.375 --> 00:43:09.628
No. but I'm being serious though.
that is so cool.

893
00:43:09.712 --> 00:43:11.839
I'm not bullshitting.
I'm being serious. too.

894
00:43:11.922 --> 00:43:13.299
He had a 12-gauge.

895
00:43:13.382 --> 00:43:15.050
-Yeah. he did.
-I don't wanna get shot.

896
00:43:15.134 --> 00:43:17.344
[laughs] He still has it. yeah. he did.

897
00:43:17.428 --> 00:43:18.679
[chuckles]

898
00:43:18.762 --> 00:43:19.972
-Hey. listen.
-Hmm.

899
00:43:20.055 --> 00:43:22.433
How about a little less paint.

900
00:43:22.516 --> 00:43:25.477
-and a little more sip?
-Okay. [chuckles]

901
00:43:29.773 --> 00:43:31.108
Hi.

902
00:43:33.485 --> 00:43:37.239
Anyway. so. Mom.
she grew up in that restaurant...

903
00:43:37.323 --> 00:43:38.449
Mmm.

904
00:43:38.532 --> 00:43:40.784
-And when she got old enough...
-Thank you.

905
00:43:40.868 --> 00:43:43.037
-She ended up running it.
-Mmm.

906
00:43:43.120 --> 00:43:45.331
Looks like that's what I'll be doing. too.

907
00:43:45.831 --> 00:43:48.876
Mmm. you don't seem too happy about that.

908
00:43:49.710 --> 00:43:51.045
[exhales]

909
00:43:51.128 --> 00:43:52.880
Well. don't get me wrong.

910
00:43:52.963 --> 00:43:54.381
I love to cook.

911
00:43:54.673 --> 00:43:55.966
So what's the problem?

912
00:43:57.635 --> 00:44:00.679
Well. I guess it's that... [sighs]

913
00:44:00.763 --> 00:44:05.768
My aspirations have taken me
a lot farther than this place.

914
00:44:05.851 --> 00:44:08.145
-Mmm.
-You know?

915
00:44:08.228 --> 00:44:12.941
I think my dreams are bigger than just...
Just running the Chicken Shack.

916
00:44:13.025 --> 00:44:14.818
Hmm.

917
00:44:14.902 --> 00:44:17.696
Well. if it means anything.

918
00:44:19.156 --> 00:44:21.742
-I'm glad you're back.
-[chuckles]

919
00:44:21.825 --> 00:44:23.410
That actually means everything.

920
00:44:23.494 --> 00:44:24.745
[giggles]

921
00:44:25.913 --> 00:44:27.956
You know. I never said it.

922
00:44:28.040 --> 00:44:32.211
but you are the only reason
I ever thought about staying.

923
00:44:33.295 --> 00:44:37.716
That's funny. because with you being gone.

924
00:44:37.800 --> 00:44:40.260
you're the only reason
I ever thought about leaving.

925
00:44:40.344 --> 00:44:42.429
-Mmm.
-[chuckles]

926
00:44:42.513 --> 00:44:44.264
-Lucky guy.
-Mmm-hmm.

927
00:44:44.348 --> 00:44:47.101
[laughing] Mmm.

928
00:44:58.070 --> 00:44:59.822
I got a double. whoo!

929
00:45:00.030 --> 00:45:02.533
Don't be a poor loser. honey.
your mama's good.

930
00:45:02.616 --> 00:45:04.493
-You taking his money. Mama?
-Yeah. baby.

931
00:45:04.576 --> 00:45:06.537
-You taking his money?
-You got to face it.

932
00:45:06.620 --> 00:45:08.080
your mama got skills.

933
00:45:08.163 --> 00:45:09.581
I think you're cheating.

934
00:45:09.665 --> 00:45:11.458
-[Mama Jay] Ain't nobody cheating.
-You are.

935
00:45:11.542 --> 00:45:12.376
-Yeah!
-Whoo!

936
00:45:12.459 --> 00:45:15.170
Yeah. you know. I figured
you tired of that hospital food.

937
00:45:15.254 --> 00:45:16.630
Yes. I am.

938
00:45:16.713 --> 00:45:18.632
-Now I'll get you some of that yard bird.
-Yeah. you made this.

939
00:45:18.715 --> 00:45:20.342
-You made this.
-[laughs] With the mashed potatoes.

940
00:45:20.426 --> 00:45:23.303
-gravy. Enjoy yourself.
-Baby. that's so sweet of you.

941
00:45:23.387 --> 00:45:25.305
-I had to do it. I had to do it.
-Mmm.

942
00:45:25.389 --> 00:45:28.100
-Hoo-wee!
-This is good.

943
00:45:28.183 --> 00:45:29.643
-I knew you'd like it.
-I knew you were gonna.

944
00:45:29.726 --> 00:45:30.936
I don't know why we're coming down here.
'Cause I knew you was gonna...

945
00:45:31.019 --> 00:45:33.188
-Baby. baby. this is good.
-[Dutch] You were gonna love that.

946
00:45:33.272 --> 00:45:34.690
-[Sonny] You really like it?
-It's amazing.

947
00:45:34.773 --> 00:45:36.650
And I was concerned
that you would have a problem

948
00:45:36.733 --> 00:45:38.652
with me kinda
